      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a flat belt conveyor?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A flat belt conveyor uses a continuous flat belt stretched between two pulleys (head and tail) to carry products on its upper surface. The belt rides on either a flat slider bed (sheet metal pan) or a roller bed (support rollers beneath the belt). Flat belt conveyors handle products of any size, shape, and bottom surface — including items too small, too soft, or too irregularly shaped for roller conveyors. They are the most versatile general-purpose conveyor type." }
    },
    {
